# npm publish allowlist is `files` in package.json (bin.ts, src, template, README).
# This .npmignore lists genuine artefacts + dev-only files to keep out of the
# published tarball; the bundled template ships verbatim.
#
# NOTE on the template's own dotfiles: npm STRIPS certain dotfiles from a published
# tarball regardless of this file — a nested `template/.gitignore` (always dropped)
# and `template/.npmrc` — and this CLI's own root `.gitignore` `.env.*` rule drops
# `template/.env.example` from `npm pack`. None of those reach a scaffold via the
# template tree, so they ship under NON-dotfile shim names (`gitignore`, `npmrc`,
# `env.example`) that survive pack, and src/scaffold.ts renames them to the real
# dotfiles at scaffold time (DOTFILE_RENAMES). scripts/verify-package.mjs guards
# both halves (shim ships; literal dotfile absent).
node_modules
/dist
*.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store
*.log

# Dev-only, never published:
test
scripts
biome.json
vitest.config.ts
tsconfig.json
.roborev.toml
suite.json
.npmrc
